Yeah, it's a shocker.

06:07.900 --> 06:09.440
What'll you have?

06:09.540 --> 06:12.130
- The usual.
- What's that?

06:12.860 --> 06:16.740
- Mustard, Coke.
- Lucy. Lucy, Lucy, Lucy.

06:16.840 --> 06:18.700
- Hi, Jerry.
- I'm glad to find you here.

06:18.800 --> 06:20.540
I was hoping you'd find me in Bermuda.

06:20.640 --> 06:22.580
Bermuda?
That's good.

06:22.680 --> 06:25.420
I am recommending you
for Employee of the Month.

06:25.520 --> 06:26.890
The usual.

06:28.130 --> 06:30.420
Really? I didn't know there was
an Employee of the Month.

06:30.520 --> 06:31.570
Yeah.

06:32.340 --> 06:35.590
"Supervisor Jerry Wallace
nominates Lucy Moderatz

06:35.690 --> 06:37.740
"for Employee of the Month.

06:38.020 --> 06:40.770
"Lucy is never tardy,
always works holidays,

06:40.870 --> 06:43.310
"even if she has worked
the previous holiday.

06:43.410 --> 06:45.150
"Just because she worked Thanksgiving,

06:45.250 --> 06:47.440
"Lucy is willing to work Christmas, too."

06:47.540 --> 06:50.250
Jerry, I'm not working Christmas.

06:52.160 --> 06:54.330
You'll get a nice plaque
with the mayor's stamp on it.

06:54.430 --> 06:56.370
- I didn't vote.
- You get to ride on a float.

06:56.470 --> 06:57.950
- Saint Paddy's Day.
- I hate parades.

06:58.050 --> 07:00.000
Did I mention extra holiday pay?

07:00.100 --> 07:02.060
- I hate you.
- Lucy.

07:03.880 --> 07:07.130
Look, Violet is sick
and Celeste can't switch

07:07.230 --> 07:09.130
because she's got some big family thing.

07:09.230 --> 07:12.130
And I promised my kids
I'd be there for them this year.

07:12.230 --> 07:13.390
It stinks, Jerry.

07:13.490 --> 07:15.820
I know it isn't fair,
and I can't make you do it.

07:17.350 --> 07:19.770
But, Lucy, you're the only one...

07:19.870 --> 07:21.450
Without family.

