I don't want any trouble.
Whoa!

09:00.660 --> 09:02.630
Let's go, let's go, let's go.

09:06.690 --> 09:08.330
Somebody help me, please.

09:08.430 --> 09:10.370
Sir? Sir? Sir?

09:10.470 --> 09:14.560
Are you okay? Can you get up?
God, sir, this is not good.

09:16.800 --> 09:20.590
Oh, God, mister...
Can you... Are you breathing?

09:20.690 --> 09:24.350
Oh, God, you smell good.
Please wake up. Please, please.

09:24.450 --> 09:26.060
Oh, God.
Can you wake up?

09:26.160 --> 09:28.580
Can you hear me?

09:29.890 --> 09:31.590
Oh, God.

09:31.940 --> 09:34.360
Wake up. Somebody help me, please.

09:34.460 --> 09:37.110
Mister?
Mister?

09:37.210 --> 09:41.090
There's a train coming, and it's fast.
It's an express.

09:42.530 --> 09:43.840
Oh, God.

09:56.340 --> 09:57.440
Hi.

10:03.720 --> 10:06.470
- All right, bring him down here.
- I need a doctor here.

10:06.890 --> 10:09.270
<i>Dr. Stevens, Dr. Jessica Stevens...</i>

10:09.370 --> 10:10.810
Hi, excuse me.

10:10.910 --> 10:12.770
About two seconds ago,
a man was brought in...

10:12.870 --> 10:14.330
- What's his name?
- I don't know it.

10:14.430 --> 10:16.440
- I need to know his name.
- He's right there.

10:16.540 --> 10:18.800
You don't know his name?
Why don't you...

10:19.070 --> 10:20.830
- You can't go in.
- You can't go in there.

10:20.930 --> 10:22.990
- You don't understand.
- You family?

10:23.090 --> 10:25.050
- Family only.
- No, you don't understand.

10:25.150 --> 10:26.920
- I was...
- You wait there.

10:29.130 --> 10:30.980
Okay, guys, what do we got here?

10:34.420 --> 10:36.230
I was gonna marry him.

10:36.430 --> 10:38.570
Get Dr. Rubin
or Dr. Ortiz here.

10:49.270 --> 10:51.780
<i>Dr. Memrack to ICU West.</i>

10:51.880 --> 10:54.000
Come on, come with me.
Over here.

11:01.620 --> 11:03.970
- Let him hear your voice, hon.
- Okay.

11:10.080 --> 11:11.180
Hi.

11:15.340 --> 11:19.760
Everything is gonna be okay. I know it.
It's gonna be fine.

11:19.860 --> 11:21.050
- Excuse me.
- Yeah?

11:21.150 --> 11:22.850
Is that the woman that saved his life?

11:22.950 --> 11:24.000
Yeah.

11:25.600 --> 11:28.910
It gets even better than that.
She's his fiancée.

11:34.780 --> 11:36.400
Excuse me, ma'am.

11:36.500 --> 11:38.570
I'm sorry, but I need to ask you
a few questions.

11:38.670 --> 11:40.220
- Okay.
- Officer, may I interrupt you?

11:40.320 --> 11:42.450
- Sure. I'll be right over there.
- Thank you.

11:42.550 --> 11:44.250
- I'm Dr. Rubin.
- Hi, I'm Lucy.

11:44.350 --> 11:46.320
Don't tell me about passes.
Where the hell is he?

11:46.420 --> 11:49.920
- Dad, don't embarrass me.
- He's so pale. Oh, my God.

11:50.020 --> 11:52.250
- What is this?
- This is my son. How is he?

11:52.350 --> 11:55.180
You can't come
bursting into this unit.

11:55.280 --> 11:58.050
- He'll be all right, right? Right?
- What happened? What's going on?

11:58.150 --> 12:00.140
- He's in a coma.
- On Christmas Day.

12:00.240 --> 12:01.260
Jesus.

12:01.360 --> 12:04.280
His vital signs are strong,
his brain waves are good.

12:04.380 --> 12:07.020
- Brain waves?
- He's going to get through this.

12:07.120 --> 12:09.290
- Are you a specialist?
- How did this happen?

12:09.650 --> 12:13.130
He was pushed from the platform
at the train station.

12:14.990 --> 12:16.410
Who's she?

12:16.510 --> 12:18.950
- She's his fiancée.
- His fiancée?

12:19.050 --> 12:20.740
- Yeah.
- Peter's fiancée?

12:20.840 --> 12:22.410
- Peter's engaged?
- Yeah, I thought...

12:22.510 --> 12:25.120
No, no, you don't understand.

12:25.220 --> 12:26.920
I mean,
he would have told us, right?

12:27.020 --> 12:28.130
Maybe he was busy.

12:28.230 --> 12:30.310
Too busy to tell his own mother
he's getting married?

12:30.410 --> 12:32.910
- Don't yell at him.
- I'm not yelling at him.

12:33.010 --> 12:35.670
- If only Jack were here.
- Grandma?

12:35.770 --> 12:38.260
- Is she okay?
- She's got a little heart problem.

12:38.360 --> 12:40.020
She's had three attacks already.

12:40.120 --> 12:43.540
They weren't attacks.
They were episodes.

12:44.020 --> 12:46.860
- Nothing wrong with her hearing.
- Excuse me, Doctor.

12:46.960 --> 12:48.520
What is she doing in here?

12:48.620 --> 12:51.000
Hey, buddy, she saved his life.

12:51.280 --> 12:53.130
You saved his life?

12:53.490 --> 12:54.700
Yeah, yeah, but...

12:54.800 --> 12:57.030
I thought he was pushed
off a train platform.

12:57.130 --> 12:58.910
She jumped on the tracks.

12:59.010 --> 13:01.140
You jumped on the tracks?

13:01.620 --> 13:04.460
Doctor, it's supposed to be family only.

13:04.560 --> 13:08.100
- She is family.
- She's the fiancée, you idiot.

13:08.200 --> 13:10.920
- Look, I'm sorry, you don't understand.
- I'm awfully sorry.

13:11.020 --> 13:14.360
We haven't seen him for a long time,
so we didn't know.

13:14.760 --> 13:17.660
I always wanted him to find a nice girl.

13:18.020 --> 13:21.030
I'm so glad he found you.

13:24.860 --> 13:26.160
Peter.

13:33.700 --> 13:35.660
- Why did you say that?
- Say what?

13:35.760 --> 13:38.290
- I'm not his fiancée.
- Why did you tell me that you were?

13:38.390 --> 13:40.500
I'm not engaged.
I've never even spoken to the guy.

13:40.600 --> 13:44.170
What? But downstairs you said...
You said you were gonna marry him.

13:44.270 --> 13:46.920
I was talking to myself.

13:47.020 --> 13:49.090
Well, next time you talk to yourself,

13:49.190 --> 13:51.690
tell yourself you're single
and end the conversation.

13:52.180 --> 13:54.890
- What am I gonna do?
- I don't know.

13:54.990 --> 13:58.560
She held me so tight.
You know, I couldn't tell her.

13:58.660 --> 14:01.200
- I know.
- Excuse me, nurse.

14:01.560 --> 14:04.190
- Is there a pharmacy in the hospital?
- What do you need?

14:04.290 --> 14:06.610
Elsie, she wants nitroglycerin.

14:06.710 --> 14:08.280
For her heart problem?

14:08.380 --> 14:09.670
Problem?

14:09.820 --> 14:11.210
Problems.

14:11.450 --> 14:14.260
You know something,
I think you saved her life.

14:14.990 --> 14:17.070
In fact, I think you saved
the whole family.

14:17.750 --> 14:19.100
Bless you.

14:19.750 --> 14:22.210
Why don't you come with me?
I'll take you down there.

14:47.820 --> 14:48.920
So,

14:49.450 --> 14:51.840
tell us how you met Peter.

14:52.160 --> 14:54.790
Ma, she doesn't wanna
talk about that now, okay?

14:54.890 --> 14:56.620
Why not?
Could use a nice story.

14:56.720 --> 14:59.170
- How do you know it was nice?
- Of course it was nice.

14:59.270 --> 15:00.630
Why shouldn't it be nice?

15:00.730 --> 15:03.210
What about that other girl?
The one he met in the bar.

15:03.310 --> 15:05.510
What's that got to do
with the price of eggs?

15:05.610 --> 15:08.440
- Ashley Bartlett Bacon.
- Ox.

15:08.600 --> 15:10.420
All I know is
she was pretty high and mighty

15:10.520 --> 15:12.790
for someone named after breakfast meat.

15:12.890 --> 15:15.120
Well, he has a nice girl now.

15:15.310 --> 15:17.330
So did you steal him from Ashley?

15:17.520 --> 15:21.090
I bet it was love at first sight. Right?

15:21.190 --> 15:23.320
I have a sense about these things.

15:23.420 --> 15:25.860
- Elsie, let her tell it.
- She is telling it.

15:25.960 --> 15:29.240
I bet that he picked you up
in that fancy car of his...

15:29.340 --> 15:32.220
What was it about him that,
you know, first struck you?

15:32.320 --> 15:35.810
- It was his, smile.
- They're caps.

15:36.130 --> 15:38.560
Six hundred bucks a tooth.

15:40.880 --> 15:44.610
Well, we saw each other

15:44.720 --> 15:48.570
and, he smiled.

15:49.180 --> 15:50.450
And...

15:51.350 --> 15:55.850
And I knew that my life
would never be the same.

15:57.480 --> 15:58.580
So...

16:03.240 --> 16:06.340
- Tomorrow night, 8:00.
- What?

16:08.290 --> 16:11.760
I got <i>Ice Capades</i>.
I know a guy.

17:25.290 --> 17:26.390
Hi.

17:38.180 --> 17:42.150
Bet you're wondering what I'm doing
here in the middle of the night?

17:43.180 --> 17:46.450
Well, I thought
I should introduce myself.

17:47.190 --> 17:48.990
My name's Lucy.

17:49.230 --> 17:51.210
Lucy Eleanor Moderatz.

17:53.570 --> 17:56.840
Think you should know
your family thinks we're engaged.

17:57.650 --> 18:01.840
Never been engaged before.
This is all very sudden for me.

18:07.540 --> 18:11.980
What I really came here to tell you
was that

18:13.550 --> 18:16.020
I didn't mean for this to happen.

18:17.050 --> 18:19.490
I don't know what to do.

18:21.600 --> 18:26.030
I mean, if you were awake,
I wouldn't be in this mess.

18:26.440 --> 18:28.910
Oh, God.
Not that I'm blaming you. Sorry.

18:29.570 --> 18:32.030
It's just that, you know,
when I was a kid,

18:32.130 --> 18:37.200
I always imagined what I would be like,

18:37.300 --> 18:41.720
or where I would be,
or what I would have when I got older.

18:41.820 --> 18:43.390
And, you know, it was the normal stuff.

18:43.490 --> 18:46.670
You know, I'd have a house and family
and things like that.

18:46.770 --> 18:49.500
You know, not that I'm complaining
or anything,

18:49.600 --> 18:51.940
because, you know, I have a cat.

18:52.220 --> 18:54.360
I have an apartment.

18:55.760 --> 18:58.990
Sole possession of the remote control.
That's very important.

18:59.600 --> 19:00.910
It's just...

19:02.140 --> 19:06.000
I never met anybody
that I could laugh with, you know?

19:12.320 --> 19:15.050
Do you believe in love at first sight?

19:15.820 --> 19:19.550
No, I bet you don't.
You're probably too sensible for that.

19:21.290 --> 19:24.210
Or have you ever, like, seen somebody,

19:24.310 --> 19:29.810
and you knew that if only that person
really knew you, they would...

19:29.920 --> 19:32.750
Well, they would of course dump
the perfect model that they were with

19:32.850 --> 19:37.820
and realize that you were the one
that they wanted to just grow old with.

19:47.680 --> 19:50.750
Have you ever fallen in love with
somebody you haven't even talked to?

19:55.830 --> 19:59.850
Have you ever been so alone you spend
the night confusing a man in a coma?

20:37.080 --> 20:42.560
<i>Brian Lynch. Mr. Brian Lynch,</i>
<i>please call Amber Lynch at 2617.</i>

20:46.840 --> 20:48.440
Oh, my God.

20:54.100 --> 20:55.200
Bye.

20:57.600 --> 21:00.730
- Lucy. We didn't know you were here.
- Hi.

21:00.830 --> 21:02.150
- Hi.
- Hi.

21:02.250 --> 21:03.980
- Were you here all night?
- Yeah.

21:04.080 --> 21:07.590
You're like me.
I could always sleep anywhere.

21:08.450 --> 21:10.510
And believe me, she has.

21:11.240 --> 21:13.260
Way to go, Gram.

21:13.620 --> 21:15.000
So how's Peter?

21:15.100 --> 21:17.270
Well, he's got more color.

21:17.440 --> 21:19.200
He has some color.
Looks like he has some color.

21:19.300 --> 21:20.350
Yeah.

21:21.060 --> 21:23.510
Well, I have to go,
so it was great to see you guys again.

21:23.610 --> 21:25.940
- Why don't you tell her? Go on, tell her.
- Yeah.

21:26.520 --> 21:29.910
We didn't get to celebrate Christmas,

21:30.270 --> 21:32.660
so it would be nice if you could join us.

21:34.730 --> 21:37.570
I would love to, but I can't.

21:37.670 --> 21:41.490
- Jack's gonna be there.
- That's right. You haven't met Jack yet.

21:41.590 --> 21:45.910
- No, not yet.
- He'll be so happy to meet you.

21:46.010 --> 21:47.040
So you'll come tonight?

21:47.140 --> 21:49.580
I really shouldn't,
because I have to work. I can't.

21:49.680 --> 21:52.710
Look, here.
Put your phone number and address there.

21:52.810 --> 21:54.590
Midge'll call you and talk you into it.

21:54.690 --> 21:55.740
Okay.

21:56.130 --> 21:58.190
Here's another card
for when you change your mind.

21:58.290 --> 22:00.180
We're in the estate-furniture business.

22:00.280 --> 22:02.360
We buy furniture from dead people.

22:03.760 --> 22:08.440
Okay. All right, well, I have it, so bye.

22:08.540 --> 22:10.580
- Bye, dear. See you later.
- Bye.

22:11.810 --> 22:14.980
- Ma'am? Excuse me, ma'am.
- What? What is this?

22:15.080 --> 22:17.440
I'm sorry, Mrs. Callaghan.
These are your husband's things.

22:17.540 --> 22:19.030
He's not my husband.

22:19.130 --> 22:21.590
I'm sorry. Your fiancé.

22:26.410 --> 22:28.680
You're Peter's fiancée?

22:30.330 --> 22:32.590
- Okay.
- Dalton Clarke.

22:32.690 --> 22:35.400
Colleague of Peter's
at Lubel, Parker, Jacobs and Fink.

22:35.720 --> 22:38.760
- I have to go now.
- He's a great guy.

22:38.860 --> 22:40.140
He's had a tough year.

22:40.240 --> 22:42.150
What with the accident
last month and all.

22:44.350 --> 22:46.980
- Accident?
- Well, of course it was an accident.

22:47.080 --> 22:50.290
I mean, it wasn't my...
Did he tell you it was my fault?

22:50.480 --> 22:54.880
We're playing basketball, all right?
I carry a pencil. I'm a lawyer, I do that.

22:54.980 --> 22:56.660
- Okay.
- Jesus, what's he...

22:56.760 --> 22:58.550
It's gonna be okay.

22:59.030 --> 23:00.780
So, what's the big deal?

23:00.880 --> 23:04.540
What's the big deal? Jerry, they
think I'm their future daughter-in-law.

23:04.640 --> 23:06.530
And the grandmother,
she's got this heart thing.

23:06.630 --> 23:09.090
If I tell the truth, she's gonna have
a heart attack and die,

23:09.190 --> 23:10.440
and it's gonna be on my head.

23:10.550 --> 23:12.550
Well, then, go along with it.

23:12.650 --> 23:14.720
And when Peter comes out of the coma,

23:14.820 --> 23:18.510
the family will be so happy,
they won't care that you lied to them.

23:18.610 --> 23:20.780
They'll probably even thank you for it.

23:21.520 --> 23:22.780
Just mustard.

23:24.270 --> 23:26.650
Okay, what if he doesn't
come out of his coma?

23:26.750 --> 23:28.440
Well, then who's to know?

23:28.540 --> 23:30.960
- I don't know.
- Now, look, look. Lucy.

23:31.110 --> 23:33.950
When my mother found out
I was getting married to my wife,

23:34.050 --> 23:35.740
her intestines exploded.

23:35.840 --> 23:37.620
- Oh, my God.
- Now, you tell them now,

23:37.720 --> 23:39.970
you might as well shoot Grandma.

23:43.160 --> 23:47.480
Come on, Mel. Mel...
Psst, psst, psst!

24:45.070 --> 24:47.000
What am I doing?

24:47.610 --> 24:48.710
Lucy.

24:49.080 --> 24:50.950
- Hi, Saul. Hi.
- You made it?

24:51.050 --> 24:53.720
- Yeah.
- How do you feel?

24:54.120 --> 24:55.580
Okay. Okay.

24:55.680 --> 24:58.720
Come on, keep me company for a while.
I don't like to smoke in the house.

24:59.080 --> 25:00.890
- Listen, you want one?
- I'm trying to quit.

25:00.990 --> 25:02.930
That's good.

25:03.250 --> 25:04.890
Here, sit down.

25:05.880 --> 25:07.670
They don't bother you, do they?

25:07.770 --> 25:09.770
No, no, I'm fine.

25:10.220 --> 25:12.820
Did you know
that I was Peter's godfather?

25:12.970 --> 25:15.360
Really?
I thought you had to be Catholic for that.

25:15.640 --> 25:17.370
Ox fudged it over.

25:17.470 --> 25:20.500
He donated 50 folding chairs
to Father Shea's bingo night.

25:21.860 --> 25:24.880
You know, being a godfather
is very important to Catholics.

25:24.980 --> 25:27.950
It means you're practically
part of the family.

25:28.050 --> 25:29.920
Well, you're lucky.

25:30.410 --> 25:33.550
It's really important to have family
around this time of year.

25:34.790 --> 25:36.220
Are you...

25:36.540 --> 25:38.620
I mean, are your parents with you?

25:38.720 --> 25:41.250
No, no.
My mom died when I was really young.

25:41.350 --> 25:43.840
And a couple years ago, my dad got sick.

25:43.940 --> 25:47.800
And we moved from Indiana to Chicago
so he could go to a research hospital.

25:47.900 --> 25:49.240
Research.

25:49.800 --> 25:52.600
A medical term for "very expensive"?

25:52.700 --> 25:57.690
Yeah. Yeah, exactly. I had to quit school
and then I started working for the CTA.

25:57.790 --> 25:59.810
And about a year ago,

25:59.910 --> 26:02.190
he decided he had had enough research,

26:02.290 --> 26:04.210
and he passed away.

26:05.400 --> 26:09.240
My wife of 51 years passed away
two years ago, February the 9th.

26:09.340 --> 26:10.660
I'm sorry.

26:10.760 --> 26:12.240
Yeah, it was a rough time for me.

26:12.340 --> 26:15.180
- Yeah.
- But Ox got me through.

26:15.330 --> 26:17.810
- You're good friends?
- The best.

26:21.380 --> 26:23.360
Lucy, the Callaghans...

26:23.670 --> 26:26.320
Well, they took me in
as part of their family.

26:27.340 --> 26:29.740
I'd never let anyone hurt them.

26:31.720 --> 26:33.410
Neither would I.

26:35.350 --> 26:36.950
I believe you wouldn't.

26:37.440 --> 26:39.960
Lucy?
You came?

26:40.360 --> 26:43.280
Hi, Saul. This is great.
Okay, come on in, you two.

26:43.380 --> 26:46.840
It's freezing out here.
Elsie made her eggnog.

26:47.120 --> 26:49.760
- Word to the wise, drink soda.
- Okay.

26:49.950 --> 26:52.850
Ox, Mom, look who's here.
Lucy came.

26:53.250 --> 26:55.040
What a surprise.

26:55.140 --> 26:58.790
- Hi, Mary.
- Come on in. It's cold out there.

26:58.890 --> 27:00.340
Oh, sweetheart.

27:00.440 --> 27:02.550
We've got the most wonderful dinner.

27:02.650 --> 27:03.760
It smells so good.

27:03.860 --> 27:04.910
Hi.

27:05.930 --> 27:07.860
This is so beautiful.

27:14.900 --> 27:17.020
- That's Peter on the right.
- He's so sweet.

27:17.120 --> 27:18.360
Yeah, the squirrels.

27:18.460 --> 27:20.130
Eggnog, everyone.

27:21.320 --> 27:23.410
Ma, where are you?
I'm serving your eggnog.

27:23.510 --> 27:25.420
I'm getting my camera.

27:25.700 --> 27:27.530
Come on, everybody.
Get close to the tree.

27:27.630 --> 27:29.390
Christmas pictures.

27:29.500 --> 27:31.000
- Lucy, come on.
- Come on, Lucy.

27:31.100 --> 27:33.020
- Let's go.
- I...

27:36.300 --> 27:38.020
Watch the birdie.

27:38.380 --> 27:40.020
Ma, take it again.
I blinked.

27:40.120 --> 27:42.730
You're lucky. I'm blind.

27:43.300 --> 27:44.680
Yeah, I love it.

27:44.780 --> 27:47.410
- Excuse me.
- I don't drink anymore.

27:48.770 --> 27:50.780
I don't drink any less either.

27:51.140 --> 27:53.660
- Perhaps I should.
- You got me on that one.

27:54.150 --> 27:55.230
Look at this.

27:55.330 --> 27:57.150
More presents.
I'll take these two.

27:57.250 --> 27:59.380
- What is this?
- Open it.

28:00.150 --> 28:02.280
- What is that?
- Turn them over.

28:02.380 --> 28:04.050
Pierced?
Really?

28:04.280 --> 28:05.660
Oh, my God, thank you.

28:05.760 --> 28:07.950
- We'll go to Wal-Mart on Monday.
- Thank you.

28:08.050 --> 28:10.780
Don't thank me. If it was up to me,
I would've gotten you a Barbie.

28:11.460 --> 28:13.280
- Did you like that?
- More presents.

28:13.790 --> 28:16.100
- We hit the jackpot.
- Mom, this is for you.

28:16.800 --> 28:19.090
"To Ox, from Uncle Al."

28:19.190 --> 28:20.510
Who the hell is Uncle Al?

28:20.610 --> 28:22.260
Uncle Al.
You know, Uncle Al from Buffalo.

28:22.360 --> 28:23.710
- You remember Al.
- Uncle Al?

28:23.810 --> 28:25.880
To Lucy, from Santa.

28:25.980 --> 28:28.600
- You remember Uncle Al.
- Remember Al? He was here.

28:28.700 --> 28:30.350
Yeah, that Uncle Al.

28:30.450 --> 28:32.960
That was
a real good Christmas.

28:33.690 --> 28:35.820
Seven bow ties, I bet.

28:35.920 --> 28:38.880
- You shouldn't have.
- That's right, she made these.

28:44.140 --> 28:48.120
The gold watch.
I love it.

28:48.220 --> 28:51.480
Sweetheart, it's so expensive.

28:51.710 --> 28:54.310
Gram, these are so great.
Thank you.

28:57.430 --> 28:59.440
They're so pretty.

29:00.760 --> 29:02.810
You remember Uncle Al,
don't you?

29:02.910 --> 29:06.060
No. Yeah, yeah.
Well, he wasn't really uncle.

29:06.160 --> 29:08.430
- I never got him anything.
- He had this moustache.

29:08.530 --> 29:10.310
He was Daddy's friend, right?

29:10.410 --> 29:12.540
- I know an Uncle Ed.
- No, Uncle Al.

29:17.030 --> 29:18.640
<i>This is Callaghan.</i>

29:18.740 --> 29:21.650
<i>Leave a message</i>
<i>and I'll get back to you. Ciao.</i>

29:22.080 --> 29:23.580
<i>Hi, it's Ashley.</i>

29:23.680 --> 29:26.920
<i>Lisbon is absolutely gorgeous,</i>
<i>but I'm cutting my trip short,</i>

29:27.020 --> 29:29.690
<i>because I have been doing</i>
<i>a lot of thinking,</i>

29:29.840 --> 29:31.670
<i>and what the hey,</i>

29:31.770 --> 29:33.440
<i>I will marry you.</i>

30:04.120 --> 30:05.220
Jack.

30:05.340 --> 30:06.980
- Hey.
- Hey, buddy.

30:10.550 --> 30:12.230
Don't wake Lucy.

30:14.590 --> 30:16.320
Who's Lucy?

30:17.060 --> 30:18.950
Lucy's Peter fiancée.

30:19.430 --> 30:22.100
No, that's not Peter's fiancée.

30:22.200 --> 30:24.040
You haven't met her?

30:24.350 --> 30:25.450
No.

30:25.700 --> 30:28.120
Well, she's great.
You're gonna love her.

30:28.820 --> 30:31.710
You know what, kid?
Maybe I'll stay the night.

30:32.120 --> 30:33.780
Don't eat my cereal
in the morning.

30:33.880 --> 30:35.450
So it's Mary's special cereal.

30:35.550 --> 30:38.130
Last time you took
the toy surprise, remember?

31:07.530 --> 31:09.090
Good morning.

31:09.280 --> 31:10.630
Oh, God.

31:11.570 --> 31:14.050
- You scared me.
- Sorry.

31:15.290 --> 31:17.140
Good morning, Jack.

31:18.410 --> 31:20.680
I guess I don't remember meeting you.

31:21.380 --> 31:24.020
Well, it's probably because
we've never met.

31:24.920 --> 31:27.020
That might have something to do with it.

31:32.510 --> 31:36.720
Cab. I have to go.
I'm really late, because I have to go.

31:36.820 --> 31:40.580
But it was nice to meet you, Jack.
So, bye.

31:42.570 --> 31:44.690
- Lucy.
- Okay, look.

31:44.790 --> 31:46.880
- I know that I...
- Hey.

31:49.110 --> 31:51.090
Welcome to the family.

31:52.410 --> 31:54.010
Thank you.

31:56.410 --> 31:57.510
Bye.

32:02.790 --> 32:05.760
We pray that the Lord's healing presence

32:05.860 --> 32:09.740
will be felt by those who are sick
and by their families.

32:10.010 --> 32:13.890
Especially Jo-Jo Goreki,
Peter Callaghan,

32:13.990 --> 32:16.580
Craig Little and Peggy Dunne.

32:17.480 --> 32:19.370
We pray to the Lord.

32:19.810 --> 32:21.940
- Lord, hear our prayer.
- Lord, hear our prayer.

32:22.040 --> 32:25.700
O, God, you call us to live as one family.

32:25.800 --> 32:28.380
- Save us from...
- So who's this Lucy?

32:28.780 --> 32:31.050
She's your brother's fiancée.

32:32.580 --> 32:35.000
You'd think
if Peter were getting married,

32:35.100 --> 32:37.180
he would have announced it
in the <i>Tribune</i>.

32:37.290 --> 32:40.190
- We read the <i>Sun Times</i>. Amen.
- Amen.

32:41.090 --> 32:43.050
So why did she sneak out this morning?

32:43.150 --> 32:44.420
She has a job.

32:44.520 --> 32:46.800
I like Mass better in Latin.

32:46.900 --> 32:49.700
It's nicer when you don't know
what they're saying.

32:50.260 --> 32:53.080
- Did you get the Bourbeau estate?
- Got it.

32:53.180 --> 32:55.270
- What about Downey's?
- Got it.

32:55.370 --> 32:57.170
- Himmelstein's?
- Yeah.

32:57.270 --> 33:00.250
- Did you get Van Allan?
- Himmelstein's took too long.

33:00.650 --> 33:03.610
- For Chrissake, Jack.
- Stop swearing.

33:03.710 --> 33:05.820
Look, you're running the business now.

33:05.920 --> 33:07.570
There's something I'd like to talk about.

33:07.670 --> 33:10.040
- Talk about that later, okay?
- Talk about it now.

33:10.140 --> 33:13.210
- He can't kill you in church.
- Will you please pipe down?

33:13.310 --> 33:15.250
Hey, be nice, pally. We're in church.

33:15.350 --> 33:17.880
- You're disrupting the Mass.
- Who made you the pope?

33:17.980 --> 33:19.030
Ox.

33:19.260 --> 33:21.940
How did Joe Kelly get to be a lector?

33:22.170 --> 33:23.720
He takes marijuana.

33:23.820 --> 33:24.870
Amen.

34:02.720 --> 34:04.340
- Hi, Luce.
- Hi, Lucy.

34:04.440 --> 34:05.740
Hi, Lucy.

34:23.159 --> 34:26.650
Come on, you stupid wing nut.
Your mother's...

34:40.690 --> 34:42.920
Excuse me, do you live here?

34:44.070 --> 34:47.420
Live here?
I own this place.

34:49.239 --> 34:53.929
Great. Well, then you would know
the woman that lives in 201.

34:54.250 --> 34:57.100
Know her?
I'm dating her.

35:36.420 --> 35:37.900
Very clean.

35:40.510 --> 35:41.780
Kitty?

35:45.350 --> 35:47.950
Kitty?
Rich kitty?

35:49.440 --> 35:51.450
Come here. Mealtime.

35:52.400 --> 35:56.370
Kitty, kitty, kitty. Kitty, kitty, kitty.

35:58.570 --> 35:59.840
Kitty.

36:02.160 --> 36:03.380
Kitty?

36:05.700 --> 36:10.720
Food. Kitty, kitty, kitty. Come here.

36:11.880 --> 36:14.770
Come here. Come on, honey.
Where are you?

36:20.430 --> 36:23.070
I'm so sorry.

36:23.390 --> 36:24.570
Nice shot.

36:27.690 --> 36:31.690
I'll get you some ice. I'm sorry.
I wasn't expecting anybody.

36:31.790 --> 36:33.660
Hey, how'd you get in here?

36:36.280 --> 36:37.370
Key?

36:37.470 --> 36:39.110
Key.
You stay here a lot?

36:39.210 --> 36:41.470
You know, feed the cat.

36:42.660 --> 36:44.760
Peter doesn't have a cat.

36:53.210 --> 36:57.220
Hello.
Hello, honey.

36:57.320 --> 37:00.780
Fluffy.
Hello, Fluffy.

37:00.880 --> 37:03.070
You must be so hungry.

37:07.020 --> 37:08.790
Are you gonna get that?

37:09.820 --> 37:12.670
No, I'm gonna let the machine get it.

37:17.660 --> 37:18.960
Hello?

37:23.410 --> 37:24.970
It's for you.

37:33.510 --> 37:34.810
Hello.

37:37.890 --> 37:40.320
Okay. Bye-bye.

37:41.730 --> 37:43.480
That was the hospital.

37:43.580 --> 37:47.620
They say it's customary for friends and
family to come down and give blood.

37:48.610 --> 37:50.370
Let's go together.

37:55.660 --> 37:58.120
You know what?
I think maybe we should take your truck.

37:58.220 --> 38:01.160
No, we ought to take Peter's car.

38:01.260 --> 38:02.310
Okay.

38:02.710 --> 38:04.260
You know where it's parked, don't you?

38:04.360 --> 38:06.980
Yeah, I... Yeah.

38:14.510 --> 38:17.320
Hey, we'll have to get
your picture for the mantel.

38:18.010 --> 38:20.280
- Of me?
- No, of you and Peter.

38:20.390 --> 38:22.780
I'm not that photogenic.

38:22.940 --> 38:24.480
I doubt that.

38:24.580 --> 38:28.070
All right, now, I want you to sit here
and sip this or you'll get woozy.

38:28.170 --> 38:29.780
When did you start seeing Peter?

38:29.880 --> 38:31.750
September 17th.

38:32.780 --> 38:36.050
- Three months. That's quick.
- You have no idea.

38:36.910 --> 38:38.660
- That's fast. That's...
- Miss.

38:38.760 --> 38:39.790
I'm fine.

38:39.890 --> 38:42.330
- That's a fast engagement.
- Wait, I'm not finished.

38:42.430 --> 38:44.480
I got it. I got it. I got it.

38:49.090 --> 38:52.300
What the hell's he got a TV for?
He's in a coma for Chrissakes.

38:52.400 --> 38:54.780
Ox. You know, he might hear you.

38:55.140 --> 38:56.970
Then get him a radio.

38:57.070 --> 38:58.640
Maybe he'd like us to sing to him.

38:58.740 --> 39:01.330
Maybe Lucy knows his favorite song.

39:01.770 --> 39:03.870
- Puff the Magic Dragon.
- Dragon.

39:04.150 --> 39:05.460
Dragon.

39:06.230 --> 39:09.000
Which one of the Three Stooges
was Peter's favorite?

39:10.320 --> 39:12.630
- Curly.
- Curly.

39:15.240 --> 39:18.250
- He's everybody's favorite.
- Well, I like Shemp.

39:18.350 --> 39:21.000
- Favorite ice cream?
- Baskin-Robbins.

39:21.100 --> 39:24.090
- Favorite baseball team?
- Chicago.

39:24.190 --> 39:25.750
Cubs or White Sox?

39:25.850 --> 39:27.730
What the heck is going on?

39:28.170 --> 39:30.530
Why are you asking her
all these questions?

39:31.180 --> 39:33.610
Don't ask me. Ask her boyfriend.

39:35.310 --> 39:36.770
That isn't very funny, you know.

39:36.870 --> 39:40.580
No, no. Not this boyfriend. Joe Fusco.

39:42.650 --> 39:43.860
Joe Jr?

39:43.960 --> 39:47.040
That's right.
Mr. Joe Fusco, Jr.

39:47.400 --> 39:49.280
He said that you were intimate.

39:49.380 --> 39:51.430
Yeah, well, he also said
he invented aluminum foil.

39:51.530 --> 39:52.780
He's delusional.

39:52.880 --> 39:54.620
He was very lucid when I talked to him.

39:54.720 --> 39:56.700
Oh, dear.
Oh, dear.

39:56.800 --> 39:59.440
- Ma, are you okay?
- You see what you did?

39:59.540 --> 40:00.630
What did I do?

40:00.730 --> 40:05.110
